Merge :
Local command used to combine branches directly.

Pull Request :
GitHub feature used to review and approve changes before merging.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MERGE vs PULL REQUEST WORKFLOW

1. MERGE (Local Git)

When used :
Used when the developer has direct access to the repository and wants to combine branches locally without review.

Procedure :
Step 1 : Switch to the target branch
git switch main : Moves to the main branch where changes will be merged.

Step 2 : Merge the feature branch
git merge Branch_1 : Combines the commits from Branch_1 into main.

Step 3 : Push the merged branch
git push : Uploads the updated main branch to GitHub.

Diagram :

Before merge

main
 │
 ├── commit A
 │
 └── Branch_1
       ├── commit B
       └── commit C


After merge

main
 │
 ├── commit A
 ├── commit B
 └── commit C

2. PULL REQUEST (GitHub)

When used :
Used when code review is required before merging changes, commonly in team projects.

Procedure :

Step 1 : Create and push the branch
git switch Branch_2
git push origin Branch_2
: Uploads the feature branch to GitHub.

Step 2 : Open GitHub repository
: Navigate to the repository page on GitHub.

Step 3 : Create Pull Request
Base branch : main
Compare branch : Branch_2
Click "Create Pull Request".

Step 4 : Review and merge
Maintainers review the changes and click "Merge Pull Request".